Concussion issues are being DOWNPLAYED by ESPN, not overblown. I've been through them and the post-concussion syndrome. I've been through just about everything (short of killing myself) that these ex-NFL'er describe. I wouldn't wish this on anyone. You may think people are making shit up, but they are not. There is no just shaking it off. Actual brain damage does not heal. Congrats to you for getting through your football days without concussions. Many of us did not. And just because you didn't go through it, doesn't mean the damage isn't real.
