The 4 players from the Saints who were given suspensions have officially appealed. One thing I completely agree with the Player's Association on is that Goddell should not be the one who hears the appeal. He shouldn't be judge, jury, executioner, and then also oversee the appeals process. The PA has filed a grievance around that to try to get someone else to take that role.The other thing the PA is claiming is that Goddell shouldn't be able to pass any judgement at all since the events in question came before the current collective bargaining agreement. I don't buy that at all.
