I think this has more to do with the publics perception of what constitutes an appeal, then it does with this particular case and the NFL's system for discipline. Doesn't the NHL have someone below the commish handing out the penalties? How is that working out for them ...I am not sure what type of system for the NFL would result in more fairness, having a panel of players, coaches and/or owners is just going to create a mess. Having a guy underneath Goodell hand them out and appeal to Goodell is just going to create a process without any real impact on the decisions (or give the league the opporuntity to backpedal on decisions based on public/NFL outrage).It is on the NFLPA, CBA, owners and coaches to make that an issue and they never seem to (at least not publicly.). The NFLPA calling foul now is a bit late to the party, and is just advocating for their players in the court of public opinion.
