I think the issue that makes it complicated (and leads to strong labor unions in pro sports in general) is the players aren't employed by the league. They're employed by the team owners, and the league is effectively a cartel the owners all belong to.There's probably no other sensible way to organize a pro sports league, but labor gets a lot more say than in a typical employer/employee situation.
